# Helm / K8s manifest rules (this repo)

## Editing templates

- Preserve existing indentation and helper usage. If the surrounding file uses `nindent 4`, match it.
- Wrap conditional manifests at the file level (`{{- if .Values.foo.enabled }}...{{- end }}`), not per-field.
- Never hand-roll labels when a helper (`chart.labels`, `chart.selectorLabels`) exists.

## Resources

- Every container MUST have `resources.requests` and `resources.limits`. Memory `requests == limits` for stateful components (mongodb, elasticsearch, rabbitmq, minio, keycloak).
- When adding a new workload, set probes explicitly. Do not rely on implicit defaults.

## Persistent volumes

- This repo supports two PV modes driven by `global.create_local_volumes`:
  - `true` — a static `PersistentVolume` with `hostPath` is emitted alongside the PVC and bound via `claimRef`. Used by k3d single-node installs (`/var/lib/tensorleap/standalone/storage/<name>`).
  - `false` — the PVC relies on a cluster `StorageClass` (via `global.storageClassName`).
- New PVCs MUST follow this dual pattern. See `charts/tensorleap/charts/node-server/templates/mongodb-pvc.yaml` as the reference.
- Do not commit PVC size reductions — shrinking is not supported.

## Elasticsearch / ECK

- The `Elasticsearch` CR lives in `charts/tensorleap/templates/elasticsearch.yaml`. The CRD is installed by `tensorleap-infra` via `eck-operator`.
- If you change `spec.version` in the Elasticsearch CR, also update the explicit `image:` field so `update-images` picks it up.
- `ES_JAVA_OPTS` heap must be ≤ 50% of the container memory limit AND ≤ 31Gi.
- `vm.max_map_count=262144` is set via a privileged initContainer on the ES pod. Keep it.

## Chart.yaml

- Bump `charts/tensorleap/Chart.yaml` `version:` on every change that affects rendered output.
- Minor-version bump (`1.5.x → 1.6.0`) signals that cluster reinstall is required (see `DEVELOPER-GUIDE.md` — the installer compares minor versions to decide reinstall).
- Dependencies are pinned to exact versions; update both the version and the bundled tarball (`helm dependency build`).

## Subcharts

- `engine`, `node-server`, `web-ui` are local subcharts edited in this repo.
- External subcharts (`ingress-nginx`, `keycloakx`, `datadog`, `eck-operator`) are configured through `values.yaml` of the parent chart using the dependency name (or alias) as the key. Do not edit the tgz contents.

## Image tags

- `image_tag` values for `engine`, `node-server`, `web-ui`, pippin are updated by the `Update images` workflow from stable tags in the respective source repos.
- When editing by hand, also update `engine-latest-image`, `node-server-latest-image`, `web-ui-latest-image`, `pippin-latest-image` at the repo root AND run `make update-images`.

## After editing charts

Run before committing:

```
make build-helm
helm lint charts/tensorleap
helm template test charts/tensorleap > /tmp/out.yaml   # inspect diff
make update-images
make validate-images
```
